-- Toulouse Beats Wasps 18-16 in Rugby's Heineken Cup; Biarritz Wins at Bath
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2010-10-10T15:52:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-10/toulouse-beats-wasps-18-16-in-rugby-s-heineken-cup-biarritz-wins-at-bath.html
Toulouse beat Wasps 18-16 in the
opening match of the four-time champion’s defense of its
Heineken Cup rugby title, while Biarritz won 12-11 at Bath.  David Skrela secured a victory for Toulouse at Stade
Ernest-Wallon with a 72nd-minute penalty in Pool 6 of European
rugby’s top club competition.   Dimitri Yachvili kicked four penalties for last season’s
runner-up Biarritz in its Pool 4 match. Ulster tops the group
after a 30-6 victory against Aironi two days ago.  Yesterday, Toulon won 19-14 against the Ospreys, London
Irish beat Munster 23-17, Cardiff Blues edged Edinburgh 18-17
and Leinster defeated Racing Metro 38-22. Clermont Auvergne beat
Saracens 25-10, Leicester Tigers topped Benetton Treviso 34-29
and Scarlets outscored Perpignan 43-34.  Two days ago, Glasgow Warriors beat Newport Gwent 21-13,
and Northampton Saints topped Castres 18-14.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  